{"author":"Iso Tester","data":{"alias":"hush-quail-holm","description":"RISK 3 (worst single unit). `reconcile_once()` in `src/rebar/_engine/rebar_reconciler/reconcile.py:556-1315` is a ~760-LOC monolith coupling snapshot-load -> diff -> apply -> persist -> log plus corrupt-snapshot abort + OM->Mutation conversion. It is stable (not actively breaking) but untestable per-phase and the highest-touch reconciler file. Decompose IN-PLACE (the natural sub-blocks are below the 100-LOC file floor, so the module-size policy prescribes in-file helpers, NOT a new module).\n\n## Why\nNo sub-phase can be tested or reused without invoking the whole orchestrator; 5-deep nested error handling lives in the spine. `_apply_batch` in applier.py (handled in the sibling Risk-2b ticket) is the related deep function.\n\n## What — in-place helper extraction along existing seams\n- Extract `_load_snapshots()`, `_run_differs()`, `_apply_mutations()`, `_persist_and_log()` as module-level (in-file) helpers; keep `reconcile_once()` as a thin sequencer that calls them in order.\n- Lift `_handle_corrupt_snapshot()` out of the spine into its own helper.\n- Preserve the single-pass IDEMPOTENT contract and the corrupt-snapshot abort semantics exactly.\n\n## Scope\nIn: behavior-preserving in-place decomposition + per-phase unit tests now made possible. Out: creating a new file (sub-blocks are <100 LOC), changing the reconcile contract, touching the acli subprocess boundary.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] `reconcile_once()` body is a thin sequencer; the four phases + corrupt-snapshot handler are separate in-file helpers.\n- [ ] At least the load/persist phases gain direct unit tests (previously impossible).\n- [ ] reconcile.py stays in the allowlist if still >800, but `reconcile_once` itself is materially shorter and max nesting drops.\n- [ ] Full reconcile idempotency + corrupt-snapshot-abort tests pass byte-for-byte.","id":"1dfc-8491-0ac0-43ff","parent_id":"5ca8-5993-ca83-40f1","priority":1,"tags":["audit-2026-06-27","oss-remediation"],"ticket_type":"story","title":"Risk 3: decompose reconcile_once() into in-place phase helpers"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1782605245269197001,"uuid":"f8d75dc9-5057-41d5-b556-65134879c15b"}